## perf (ontology/pitfalls): eliminate taxonomy fetch spinner

### Context
On every page load `PitfallsModule.init()` fired a `fetch('/ontology/pitfalls/taxonomy')`
round-trip which triggered a lazy import of `runner.py` (sentence-transformers,
nltk, sklearn try/except block) on the backend — causing a noticeable delay and
a spinner before the pattern list appeared.

The taxonomy is a **static, hardcoded list of 19 pitfalls** (P1.1–P4.7) that
never changes at runtime. Moving it to the JS constant `STATIC_TAXONOMY` (a
direct copy of `PITFALL_TAXONOMY` from `runner.py`) eliminates the round-trip
and the spinner entirely — patterns appear instantly on section open.

### Changes

1. `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-pitfalls.js`
   - Added `STATIC_TAXONOMY` constant (19 entries, mirrors `runner.py`).
   - Replaced `_loadTaxonomy()` (async fetch) with a synchronous inline
     assignment: `_taxonomy = STATIC_TAXONOMY; _renderPatternSelector(); selectAll();`
   - Removed `_loadTaxonomy()` function entirely.

2. `src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_pitfalls.html`
   - Removed the loading spinner inside `#pitfallsPatternBody` (no longer needed).

### Modified files
- `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-pitfalls.js`
- `src/front/templates/partials/ontology/_pitfalls.html`

### Test results
7/7 pitfalls agent tests pass. No regressions.

