## fix (mcp/agent): MCP server tool descriptions missing inferred-data guidance

### Context
Both Graph Chat and the MCP server already read the union view
(`g_<dom>_v<n>` = `_sync UNION ALL __app`), so materialized/inferred
triples are always reachable via `describe_entity` and `list_entity_types`.

The problem: the MCP server's FastMCP `instructions` string and tool
docstrings contained no guidance on which tools see inferred data and
which don't. An external LLM client would default to `query_graphql`
(schema-filtered, misses inferred predicates not in the ontology) rather
than `describe_entity` (raw triple store, sees everything).

Graph Chat already had the correct guidance in its `SYSTEM_PROMPT`
(lines 67–105 of `engine.py`) — this fix brings the MCP server to parity.

### Changes

1. `src/mcp-server/server/app.py`
   - `FastMCP(instructions=...)`: expanded with a DATA SOURCES section
     explaining `describe_entity` = ground truth (union view, all triples
     including inferred), `query_graphql` = schema-only (may miss inferred
     predicates), and a DECISION RULE to always prefer `describe_entity`
     for entity-level questions.
   - `describe_entity` docstring: added explicit note that it queries the
     raw triple store union view and is the primary tool for inferred data.
   - `query_graphql` docstring: added WARNING that inferred/materialised
     predicates not declared in the ontology are silently invisible.

### Modified files
- `src/mcp-server/server/app.py`

### Test results
122/122 agent unit tests pass.

