## Inferred-data visibility: stats signal + explicit LLM hint

### Context
Agents (Graph Chat, MCP server) were not reliably surfacing inferred/reasoning
triples to the LLM because the LLM had no way to know that inferred data existed
before choosing a query tool.  Without a visible signal, it would fall back to
`run_sparql` (warehouse Delta view — no inferred data) or `query_graphql`
(schema-filtered — may miss inferred predicates not in the ontology).  GraphQL
worked because users tested it directly, bypassing the LLM tool-selection step.

### Changes
1. `src/back/core/triplestore/TripleStoreBackend.py` — added
   `get_inferred_triple_count(table_name)` method (default returns 0).
2. `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/LakebaseFlatStore.py` — overrides
   `get_inferred_triple_count` to `COUNT(*)` from the `*__app` companion table
   directly.
3. `src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py` — `/dtwin/sync/stats` now queries
   `get_inferred_triple_count` and includes `inferred_triples` in the response.
4. `src/api/routers/digitaltwin.py` — `StatsResponse` model gains
   `inferred_triples: int = 0`; `/api/v1/digitaltwin/stats` includes the field.
5. `src/agents/agent_dtwin_chat/tools.py` — `tool_list_entity_types` renders
   `"Inferred triples: N  [reasoning output — ONLY visible via describe_entity,
   NOT via query_graphql or run_sparql]"` when N > 0.
6. `src/mcp-server/server/app.py` — `list_entity_types` renders the same hint
   when `inferred_triples > 0`.

### Modified files
- `src/back/core/triplestore/TripleStoreBackend.py`
- `src/back/core/graphdb/lakebase/LakebaseFlatStore.py`
- `src/api/routers/internal/dtwin.py`
- `src/api/routers/digitaltwin.py`
- `src/agents/agent_dtwin_chat/tools.py`
- `src/mcp-server/server/app.py`

### Test results
845/846 tests pass. 1 pre-existing failure in `test_permissions.py`
(`test_app_and_workspace_caches_are_isolated`) unrelated to these changes.

