## Graph Chat: remove run_sparql to guarantee all data is always visible

### Context
The `run_sparql` tool in Graph Chat translates SPARQL to SQL over the Databricks
warehouse Delta views — which only contain the synced (`_sync`) data and never
include inferred/materialised triples from the `__app` companion table.  When the
LLM chose `run_sparql` for entity or relationship queries (a common pattern), the
results silently excluded all reasoning output, giving the impression that Graph
Chat "respected" the Inferred checkbox.  The checkbox does NOT technically affect
Graph Chat's data path, but the LLM's tool choice did.

### Changes
1. `src/agents/agent_dtwin_chat/tools.py` — removed `_RUN_SPARQL_DEF` from
   `TOOL_DEFINITIONS` and `run_sparql` from `TOOL_HANDLERS` so the LLM can only
   use `describe_entity` (raw union view) and `query_graphql` (schema-filtered
   union view) — both of which always include inferred data.
2. `src/agents/agent_dtwin_chat/engine.py` — removed the `run_sparql` tool entry
   from the system prompt TOOLS section and WORKFLOW step 3 reference.

### Modified files
- `src/agents/agent_dtwin_chat/tools.py`
- `src/agents/agent_dtwin_chat/engine.py`

### Test results
122/122 agent unit tests pass.

