## Fix unit test suite — mock-patch path shadowing and missing optional deps

### Context
Running the full unit test suite revealed 23 pre-existing test failures caused by two categories of issues:
1. `__init__.py` re-exports in `back.core.databricks` and `back.objects.registry` shadow the submodule names, causing `mock.patch("pkg.Module.Class", ...)` to resolve `pkg.Module` to the CLASS instead of the module, then fail to find `Class` on it.
2. Optional dependencies (`psycopg`, `apscheduler`) not installed in the local venv caused tests to short-circuit before reaching the mocked code.

### Changes
1. `tests/units/core/test_health.py` — add `_VFS_MOD` / `_LBA_MOD` via `importlib.import_module`; replace 5 `patch(string)` calls with `patch.object(module, attr)` (11 tests fixed).
2. `tests/units/auth/test_permissions.py` — add `_PS_MOD` via `importlib`; replace 7 `patch(string)` calls with `patch.object` (5 tests fixed).
3. `tests/units/settings/test_graph_engine_config.py` — add `_db_auth_mod` / `_uc_mod` via `importlib`; replace 2 `patch(string)` calls with `patch.object` (1 test fixed).
4. `tests/units/settings/test_settings_lakebase_status.py` — add `patch.dict(sys.modules, {"psycopg": MagicMock()})` to 3 tests that require psycopg to be "available" (3 tests fixed).
5. `tests/units/registry/test_registry.py` — add `@pytest.mark.skipif(not find_spec("apscheduler"), ...)` to `TestSchedulerResolveCredsLakebase` (3 tests skipped cleanly instead of erroring).

### Modified files
- `tests/units/core/test_health.py`
- `tests/units/auth/test_permissions.py`
- `tests/units/settings/test_graph_engine_config.py`
- `tests/units/settings/test_settings_lakebase_status.py`
- `tests/units/registry/test_registry.py`

### Test result
2024 passed, 15 skipped in 238.24s — zero failures.
E2E: 257 passed in 110.35s — zero failures.

