## Simplify HTTP User-Agent to plain "ontobricks"

### Context
The `User-Agent` header was set to `OntoBricks/<version>` (e.g. `OntoBricks/0.4.0`). Changed to the simpler lowercase string `ontobricks` — no version, no capitalisation — consistent with how the app identifies itself in other contexts (logger name, graph name, session cookie).

### Changes
1. `src/shared/config/constants.py` — `HTTP_USER_AGENT` now a fixed string `"ontobricks"` instead of `f"{APP_NAME}/{APP_VERSION}"`.
2. `src/mcp-server/server/app.py` — local `_USER_AGENT` changed from `"OntoBricks-MCP/1.0.0"` to `"ontobricks"`.

